  "_note": "Per-scheme villain-deck composition counts (WP-167 / WP-169 / D-16702 / D-16803). Keys: setAbbr -> schemeSlug -> { villainDeckTwistCount?, villainDeckBystanderCount? }. (i) Each entry must carry AT LEAST ONE of the two counts and may carry only one (D-16803). (ii) An omitted count keeps that scheme's engine default: 8 twists (D-1411) / numPlayers bystanders (D-1412); a scheme absent from this file emits neither field and falls back to both defaults. (iii) Producers: convert-cards-v15.mjs applies these to the 36 npm-derived sets; apply-card-counts.mjs applies them to the 4 outlier sets (2099, amwp, wpnx, wtif). (iv) Counts are extracted from each scheme's committed printed 'Setup:' text in data/cards/*.json; villainDeckTwistCount is the number of Twists shuffled INTO the villain deck (Twists placed next to the Scheme are excluded), and villainDeckBystanderCount is the explicit villain-deck bystander count (including an explicit 0). (v) Schemes whose printed villain-deck twist count is player-count-dependent, additive-per-player, or otherwise not a single constant are CARVED OUT (not encoded) and keep the 8-twist fallback pending a per-player representation (D-16804). Both converters loud-fail (full-sentence error, non-zero exit) on a slug matching no scheme in the set, or on an entry carrying neither count.",
